label: adjunct characteristic of food (RENAME)
definition: A data item consisting of a claim or record of a food product's origin or processing history or suitability for some purpose.

label: sustainable agriculture
definition: Farming in a sustainable way, which means meeting society's present food and other harvested product needs without compromising the ability for current or future generations to meet their needs.

parent class: food product by process|agricultural production factor
label: sustainable agriculture food product
definition: A food product produced by sustainable agricultural practices.

parent class: plant food product|sustainable agriculture food product
label: plant-based meat product analog
definition: A food product designed to taste like animal meat but which is made from plant food sources.

parent class: food product by process|sustainable agriculture food product
label: cell-based technology food product
definition: A food product made from plant or animal cell lines incubated in a production facility.

parent class: harvested food material|sustainable agriculture food product
label: food harvested by hunting
definition: food material that is obtained by hunting, the practice of seeking, pursuing and capturing or killing wild animals.

parent class: harvested food material|sustainable agriculture food product
label: food harvested by gathering
definition: Food material that is obtained by foraging the natural environment for food.

label: food (genetically-modified)
definition: A food product which is produced from an organism which has changes in its DNA as a result of genetic engineering.

label: food (not genetically-modified)
definition: A food product which is produced from one or more organisms, none of which have changes in their DNA as a result of genetic engineering.

label: food production proximity to consumer distrobution
country-of-origin datum
definition: A data item about the country or countries of manufacture, production, design, or brand origin where an article or product comes from. For multinational brands, this may include multiple countries within the value-creation process.

label: single-country-of-origin datum
definition: A product primarily manufactured in a single country of origin, and with components coming from that country.

label: American-made product datum
definition: A product primarily manufactured within America.

label: food retailed within its country-of-origin datum
definition: A single-country-of-origin food product which is retailed in that country.

parent class: food retailed within its country-of-origin datum
label: local food datum
definition: Food produced within a relatively short distance of where it is consumed.

label: wild harvested animal
definition: An organism that originated from a wild caught population.

label: semidomestic or semiwild food production environment
domestic or cultivated food production environment

parent class: domestic or cultivated food production environment
label: outdoor/open-air growing condition

parent class: domestic or cultivated food production environment
label: controlled environment agriculture (CEA)
definition: A technology-based approach toward food production in which  growing conditions are optimized within an enclosed growing structure such as a greenhouse or building throughout the development of a crop.

label: tunnel farming / polytunnel farming process
exact synonym: tunnel production; A polytunnel (also known as a polyhouse, hoop greenhouse or hoophouse, grow tunnel or high tunnel)

label: conventional under glass/protected production growing condition
organic under glass/protected production growing condition
